    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-12-15T18:01:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-12-15T18:01:00-05:00" n="309"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">771.00/12–1452: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d309fn1">This telegram was drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_CLG1">Cyr</persName> (<gloss target="#t_AF1">AF</gloss>) and
                        cleared in <gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_NEA1"
                            >NEA</gloss>. <persName corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName> (<gloss
                            target="#t_G1">G</gloss>) signed for the Acting Secretary. It was
                        repeated to Tangier, Rabat, and Casablanca.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-12-15T18:01:00-05:00"
                            >December 15, 1952—6:01 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3401. Supplementing Tangier <gloss target="#t_Legtel1">Legtel</gloss> 240, Dec.
                        14,<note n="2" xml:id="d309fn2">
                        <ref target="#d308">
                            <ref target="#d308">
                                <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                            </ref>
                        </ref>.</note> 35 to Paris, Balafredj has informed <gloss target="#t_USUN1"
                        >USUN</gloss> official that he reed <gloss target="#t_msg1">msg</gloss> Sun
                    from Sultan than remaining Istiqlal leaders have been rounded up and he himself
                    is in imminent danger being deposed. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>
                    queried <gloss target="#t_Con1">Con</gloss> Rabat Sun this matter.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d309fn3">Telegram 53 to Rabat, Dec. 14, not printed.
                        (771.00/12–1452)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Today <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> reports that Balafredj is
                    broadcasting this news at UN and that Indo <gloss target="#t_REP1">Rep</gloss>
                    mentioned it this morning in UN debate. <persName corresp="#p_LF1"
                        >La-Coste</persName> says story is nonsense but that he is not in position
                    make official statement for Fr Govt. <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> also
                    reports Balafredj addressing plea to Secy on this subj.</p>
                <p>In light of foregoing, Secy may wish take occasion when mtg with <persName
                        corresp="#p_SR1">Schuman</persName> to express informally opinion that
                    recent Fr public disavowal of intention to depose <persName corresp="#p_BPC1"
                        >Bey</persName> of Tunis is having quieting effect on North <gloss
                        target="#t_AF1">Af</gloss> situation and that he presumes Fr Govt entertains
                    similar intention toward Sultan of Morocco. Since we understand from <gloss
                        target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> that tone Morocco debate more serious in
                    criticism of Fr than Tunisian discussion,<note n="4" xml:id="d309fn4">For the
                        documentation on Tunisia, see <ref target="#pg_665">pp. 665</ref> ff.</note>
                    presumably Fr public statement denying rumor of plans to depose Sultan wld be
                    even more useful. Since in absence of Fr from North <gloss target="#t_AF1"
                        >Af</gloss> debates in UN US has had to accept more active role in debate
                    than we wld have desired, we feel justified approaching Fr this matter.</p>
                <p>If Secy approves this suggestion, he may prefer have <gloss target="#t_Emb1"
                        >Emb</gloss> approach <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> in this
                    vein.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
